2. What You Are Doing Correctly
A. Centralized Identity Provider (Google Workspace)

Correct approach.

Why:

Single source of truth
Easy onboarding/offboarding
Central governance
Enterprise MFA policies

This avoids:

Separate Databricks users/passwords

which is bad practice.

3. SAML for Authentication

Correct.

SAML SSO is standard enterprise authentication for Databricks.

Flow:

User → Google Login → MFA → Databricks

Good because:

No local credentials
Centralized authentication
Security compliance
4. SCIM Provisioning

VERY good approach.

This is one of the most important parts.

Why:

Automatic user creation
Automatic deactivation
Automatic group synchronization

Without SCIM:

Manual user management becomes nightmare.

For a global Holcim project, SCIM is essential.

5. Group-Based Access Control

This is the MOST correct thing in your design.

You are using:

Google Groups → Databricks Groups → Permissions

This is exactly how enterprise governance should work.

You should NEVER do:

GRANT SELECT TO rajesh@company.com

Instead:

GRANT SELECT ON SCHEMA finance TO finance_analyst_group;

That is scalable.

6. Unity Catalog Based Permissions

Correct and modern.

Unity Catalog should become:

Central governance layer
Fine-grained security layer

This is MUCH better than:

Legacy Hive Metastore ACLs
Workspace-local permissions
7. What I Think You SHOULD Structure Properly

This is where many projects fail.

8. Recommended Access Model

You should structure permissions in layers.

Layer 1 — Workspace Access

Controls:

Who can log into workspace

Examples:

Group	Access
de-emea	EMEA Workspace
ds-global	DS Workspace
analysts-finance	SQL only

This is coarse-grained access.

Layer 2 — Catalog Access

Controls:

Domain-level access

Example:

finance_catalog
sales_catalog
manufacturing_catalog

Permissions:

GRANT USE CATALOG
Layer 3 — Schema Access

Controls:

Functional segmentation

Example:

finance.raw
finance.staging
finance.gold
Layer 4 — Table/View Access

Controls:

Sensitive datasets

Example:

GRANT SELECT ON VIEW finance.customer_masked
Layer 5 — Row/Column Level Security

VERY important for enterprise.

Especially:

HR
Finance
Regional data restrictions

Example:

APAC users only see APAC data
Salary columns masked

Unity Catalog supports:

Row filters
Column masking

You should definitely include this in design.

